<seg id=1> Ding Hao Becomes the First Handicapped University Student Grown Up in An Orphanage in China </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Hangzhou, September 1, Telegram (Reporter Zhu Guoxian, Trainee Guan Zhehui).  Ding Hao, a handicapped student who has been an orphan since childhood and grown up in Hangzhou Children's Orphanage, received notice of admission from Hangzhou University a few days ago to become a student of the university's Department of Philosophy and Social Science. </seg>
<seg id=3> It is reported that the 19-year old Ding Hao is the first university student of handicapped orphan adopted by and grew up in an orphanage since the founding of New China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> "I wish I could have jumped up when I received the notice of admission", said Ding Hao. However, he was unable to "jump" to express his mood of excitement. </seg>
<seg id=5> Ding Hao had a high fever when he was three years old, causing him to suffer from a serious sequelae of infantile paralysis. In the same year, he was adopted by an orphanage. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Ding Hao finished his primary school at the Children's Orphanage. Soon afterwards, he enrolled in a secondary school in a nearby village. </seg>
<seg id=7> At the beginning, Ding Hao was escorted by teachers of the Orphanage. When he entered second grade, he boarded at school and went back to the Orphanage every Saturday. He never missed a class regardless of wind or rain.  </seg>
<seg id=8> This year, he participated in college entrance examination and was admitted with qualified result by Hangzhou University. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Ding Hao's success is an embodiment of painstaking care by all circles of the society. </seg>
<seg id=10> For the past 16 years, the Children's Orphanage has been taking good care of him. Since last year, the Orphanage has spent more than 3000RMB for his tuition, study materials, and nutriment alone. </seg>
<seg id=11> All circles of the society have also lent a helping hand to him.  </seg>
<seg id=12> After hearing the news that Ding Hao was admitted to university, Hangzhou Longchang Grain & Oil Trading Company donated 20,000RMB to sponsor his study. Meanwhile, an artificial limb factory donated a wheelchair and walking sticks to him.  </seg>
</p>
